{"id":1191296219,"question_id":463,"lang":"cpp","lang_name":"C++","time":"1 week, 3 days","timestamp":1709364772,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"72 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1191296219/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Island Perimeter","memory":"100.8 MB","code":"class Solution {\npublic:\n    int dx[4] = {0, 1, 0, -1}, dy[4] = {1, 0, -1 ,0};\n    int islandPerimeter(vector<vector<int>>& grid) {\n        int ans = 0;\n        for(int i = 0; i < grid.size(); i++){\n            for(int j = 0; j < grid[0].size(); j++){\n                if(grid[i][j]){\n                    int tmpans = 4;\n                    for(int k = 0; k < 4; k++){\n                        int nx = i + dx[k], ny = j + dy[k];\n                        if(nx > -1 && nx < grid.size() && ny > -1 && ny < grid[0].size() && grid[nx][ny] == 1) tmpans--;\n                    }\n                    ans += tmpans;\n                }\n            }\n        }\n        return ans;\n    }\n};","compare_result":"","title_slug":"island-perimeter","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
